techmeme.title: Alphabet reports YouTube's Q3 ad revenue rose 15% YoY to $10.26B, vs. $10.01B est., and Google's advertising revenue reached $74.18B, up from $65.85B a year ago (Todd Spangler/Variety)
Microsoft reports Q1 revenue up 18% YoY to $77.7B, vs. $75.3B est., net income up 12% to $27.7B, and Azure and other cloud services revenue up 40% (Microsoft)
Meta reports Q3 revenue up 26% YoY to $51.2B vs. $49.4B est., net income down 83% to $2.7B due to a $15.9B one-time income tax charge; META down 6%+ after hours (Meta)
Alphabet reports Q3 revenue up 16% YoY to $102.35B, vs. $99.89B est., Cloud revenue up 34% to $15.16B, net income up 33% to $34.98B; GOOG jumps 5%+ after hours (Alphabet)
Google starts rolling out the Gemini for Home voice assistant in early access in the US, on Nest devices set to English (Abner Li/9to5Google)
